The paper focuses on the development of a platform for research in embodied AI, specifically for training virtual robots in 3D simulation before transferring the learned skills to reality. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The platform also involves handling 3D datasets and using sensors, which relates to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the platform allows for benchmarking and testing, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY).
